<item>
            <title>[SOLR-12416] router.autoDeleteAge is not accepted in CREATEALIAS command</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-12416</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve been experimenting with time routed aliases, specifically with the autoDeleteAge feature (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-11925&quot; title=&quot;Auto delete oldest collections in a time routed alias&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-11925&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-11925&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) and notice that the router.autoDeleteAge parameter was silently ignored in the CREATEALIAS command.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using ALIASPROP to set it worked just fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem seems to be that&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/lucene-solr/blob/bf6503ba5871228692ca79f0b2204a935538e00a/solr/core/src/java/org/apache/solr/cloud/api/collections/TimeRoutedAlias.java#L83&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;TimeRoutedAlias.OPTIONAL_ROUTER_PARAMS&lt;/a&gt;&#160;has not been updated when the autoDeleteAge property was added.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Experimenting with a freshly downloaded Solr 7.3.1&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
